{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the left.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to zero and its ","type":"text"},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to half the height of the view.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"remoteSource":{"fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159"},"title":"centerOffset"},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"MLNAnnotation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","type":"topic","title":"centerOffset","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"title":"MLNAnnotationView","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotationView"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object that corresponds to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"}}}